body_html:
I need the tf.stack to flatten the columns from the CSV file. Anyway I removed the tf.stack as shown below:

dataset= tf.contrib.data.make_csv_dataset(file_name,48,select_columns=['Load_residential_multi_0','Load_residential_multi_1'],shuffle=False)
dataset = dataset.batch(2)
get_iterator = dataset.make_one_shot_iterator()
get_batch = get_iterator.get_next()

But I get pretty much the same error except that the tf.contrib.data.make_csv_dataset is now returning an ordered dictionary.

ValueError: Please provide data as a list or tuple of 2 elements - input and target pair. Received OrderedDict([('Load_residential_multi_0', <tf.Tensor 'IteratorGetNext_8:0' shape=(?, ?) dtype=float32>), ('Load_residential_multi_1', <tf.Tensor 'IteratorGetNext_8:1' shape=(?, ?) dtype=float32>)])

Maybe the tf.contrib.data.make_csv_dataset just can't work with Keras model. I wish they would clarify.

body:
I need the tf.stack to flatten the columns from the CSV file. Anyway I removed the `tf.stack` as shown below: 
```
dataset= tf.contrib.data.make_csv_dataset(file_name,48,select_columns=['Load_residential_multi_0','Load_residential_multi_1'],shuffle=False)
dataset = dataset.batch(2)
get_iterator = dataset.make_one_shot_iterator()
get_batch = get_iterator.get_next()
```
But I get pretty much the same error except that the  `tf.contrib.data.make_csv_dataset` is now returning an ordered dictionary.

> ValueError: Please provide data as a list or tuple of 2 elements  - input and target pair. Received OrderedDict([('Load_residential_multi_0', <tf.Tensor 'IteratorGetNext_8:0' shape=(?, ?) dtype=float32>), ('Load_residential_multi_1', <tf.Tensor 'IteratorGetNext_8:1' shape=(?, ?) dtype=float32>)])

Maybe the tf.contrib.data.make_csv_dataset just can't work with Keras model. I wish they would clarify.
